# Verification Checklist - Sprint Relay Debugger

## 1. Sprint Filter
- [ ] Header shows sprint dropdown with date ranges (e.g., "Sprint 11 · Mar 2 – Mar 13").
- [ ] Sprint 11 is auto-selected (matching current date Mar 6, 2026).
- [ ] Blue badge showing sprint date range next to the dropdown.
- [ ] Screenshot of the header area.

## 2. Personnel View
- [ ] Personnel view is the default tab.
- [ ] Person cards show tasks with colored priority dots.
- [ ] Tasks are sorted by status priority (Reprocess > Waiting to Integrate > In Process > Not Started > others > Staging Passed).
- [ ] Screenshot of a person card.

## 3. Task Inspector
- [ ] Clicking a task opens the side inspector panel.
- [ ] "Assigned People" section with rounded badges.
- [ ] "Daily Meeting Notes" section and "Add Today's Note" button.
- [ ] Screenshot of the inspector.

## 4. Meeting Note Form
- [ ] Clicking "Add Today's Note" button opens the form.
- [ ] Form has "Is this task stalled?" toggle.
- [ ] "Blocked By" dropdown has "Assigned on this task" and "Team Leaders" groups.
- [ ] "Solution / Action Plan" textarea.
- [ ] Screenshot of the open form and dropdown options.
